  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the people gave a shout,.... At the end of the oration; these were flatterers, as Josephus says in the place before referred to, who cried out one from another, saluting him as God; saying, be merciful to us, hitherto we have revered thee as a man, henceforward we confess thee somewhat more excellent than mortal nature: and so it follows here, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying it is the voice of a God, and not of a man; the Vulgate Latin version reads, \"the voices of God and not men\"; and the Ethiopic version, \"the city shouted in, or with the voice of God\", with the voice of man; as if this referred to the acclamation of the people, and not the speech of the king; very wrongly. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "saying it is the voice of a God, and not of a man; the Vulgate Latin version reads, \"the voices of God and not men\"; and the Ethiopic version, \"the city shouted in, or with the voice of God\", with the voice of man; as if this referred to the acclamation of the people, and not the speech of the king; very wrongly. ",
            "children": []
          },
